Reese先生 只要你准备好了
Whenever you're ready, Mr. Reese.

21
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:09,400
我就在这里
I'm in here.

22
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,400
你从哪来?
Where did you come from?

23
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,900
我突破了时空连续统一体
I breached the space-time continuum.

24
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,200
不是真的
Not really.

25
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:23,000
我确实感觉到隐私被侵犯了
I did sense my privacy being invaded.

26
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,700
但现在先不谈这个 我们还有工作要做
But we'll leave that for now. We have work to do.

27
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,000
号码们出来了
Numbers have come in.

28
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,500
- 号码们 什么意思? - 复数的通用意思
What do you mean, numbers? What plurals usually mean.

29
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:29,900
多于一个
More than one.

30
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,200
这次是4个
In this case four.

31
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:35,600
Claire Ryan 42岁 纽约大学讲师
Claire Ryan, 42, lecturer at NYU.

32
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Matt Duggan 33岁 服务生
Matt Duggan, 33, a waiter.

33
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:40,200
Wendy McNally 29岁 发型师
Wendy McNally, 29, a hairstylist.

34
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:42,600
还有Paula Vasquez 23岁 待业
And Paula Vasquez, 23, unemployed.

35
