所以这四个里可能有一个想干掉另外三个
So one of these four could be trying to kill the other three.

39
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,300
或者他们可能都是受害者或是杀手
Or they could all be victims or all killers.

40
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:58,600
或者如你所说 都是随机的
Or as you say, all random.

41
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:00,400
不论是哪一种 我们都需要赶快行动
Either way, we need to move fast.

42
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:03,100
虽然只差1毫秒 Claire Ryan的数据是最先出现的
Claire Ryan's number came up first if only by a millisecond.

43
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:06,300
皇后区威尔逊242号3C室
242 Wilson in Queens, apartment 3C.

44
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,800
说到隐私
Speaking of privacy.

45
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,900
对你寻找的或可能找到的小心些 Reese先生
Careful what you look for, Mr. Reese, or you might find it.

46
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,900
坦白说
We have to be straight with you.

47
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,100
有些事情是不合情理的
Some things don't add up.

48
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:27,100
比如?
Like what?

49
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,400
你去见你的秘密线人
You go to meet your confidential informant,

50
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:34,500
Nashus Drake 绰号"瓶盖" 对你来说是可信任的消息来源
one Nashus Drake, AKA "Bottlecap"- According to you a trusted source.

51
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,200
他枪击你的胸部
He shoots you in the chest.

52
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,200
幸运的是你穿着防弹背心
Luckily, you're wearing a vest.

53
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:42,100
他在受到不明枪手枪击的时候想杀你的?
He's gonna kill you when he gets shot by an unknown shooter?

54
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,900
正如我陈述中所说的
Like it says in my statement.

55
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:47,800
你的陈述中没有说 这个不明枪手来自哪里
Your statement doesn't say where this unknown shooter came from.

56
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,200
因为我不知道
Because I don't know.

57
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,600
这里也没说他为什么要这么做
It also doesn't say why he did it.

58
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:54,200
也许是因为他看到我要被枪击了
Maybe because he saw me about to get shot.

59
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,600
那么他关心你
So he cares about you.

60
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,500
我怀疑他对我会有任何的兴趣
I doubt he gives a damn about me.

61
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:01,000
但这是你最近三个月一直在追的人啊
But this is the man you've been chasing for the last three months.

62
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,100
正如我陈述中所说的 我相信如此
As it says in my statement, I believe so.

63
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:06,862
所以呢 这个你据说一直在试图逮捕的人
So what, this guy allegedly you've been trying to lock up, - he saves your life? - "Allegedly."

64
00:04:06,862 --> 00:04:09,521
- 救了你的命? - "据说"

65
00:04:09,521 --> 00:04:10,500
很聪明
That's clever.

66
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,000
你知道怎样才叫聪明么?
You know what would be clever?

67
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:15,600
你假装追捕这个人 但事实上你在为他工作
You pretending to chase this guy when in fact you're working for him.

68
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,300
我想我们谈完了
I think we're done here.

69
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,200
探员 告诉我
Detective, tell me something.

70
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,000
他有和你联系么?
Has he made contact with you?

71
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,600
和你说过话?
Spoken to you?

72
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:29,100
我的陈述你们已经拿到了
You got my statement.

73
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:33,300
除非我的委托人在场 不然我们不会再交谈
We don't talk again unless my delegate is present.

74
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,800
所以他来回踱步 来回 来回
So he's pacing back and forth, back and forth, back and forth.

75
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:43,300
终于脱掉面具 直走进门 把他自己撞晕
Finally pulls his mask down, walks right into the door, knocks himself out cold.

76
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:46,200
这天才忘记在面具上留眼窝了
The genius forgot to cut the eyeholes in the mask.

77
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,300
嘿 Carter
Hey, Carter.

78
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,400
你在做什么? 你被枪击了
What are you doing? You got shot.

79
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,600
为了Pete 休息一下
Take some time off, for Pete's sake.

80
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:56,400
我的防弹衣被击中了 它可以休息
My vest got shot. It can take some time off.

81
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:00,000
调查什么的进行得怎么样了?
How's it going with the inquiry and everything?

82
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,400
老样子
The way these things usually go.

83
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,600
让你觉得谋杀了自己的亲生母亲一样
They make you feel like you murdered your own mother.

84
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:06,900
所以我被困在了办公桌上 而你要和Olson一起工作
So I'm stuck on my desk and you're working with Olson.

85
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,900
太好了 探员的快乐
Oh, great. Detective happy.

86
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,400
- 你怎么跟他们说秘密线人的? - 实话实说
What did you tell 'em about the CI? The truth.

87
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,600
他被不知名的枪手带走了
He was taken out by an unknown shooter.

88
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,200
那个人...你这次看清楚了么?
The guy- You got a good look at him this time, didn't you?

89
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,300
没 脸没有
No. Not his face.

90
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:20,400
这也许是件好事
Well, maybe that's a good thing.

91
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:22,000
你知道 这会很难
'Cause you know, it would be hard.

92
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,200
你都不知道到底该感谢他还是逮捕他
You don't know whether to thank the guy or arrest him.

93
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:30,200
不 很简单 我会逮捕他
No, that'd be easy. I'd arrest him.

94
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,700
听着 不论发生了什么或是你需要什么
Look, whatever happens or you need anything, - I got your back, all right? - Okay.

95
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,880
- 我都会支持你 好么? - 好的

96
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,400
Finch 我在Claire的公寓里
Finch, I'm at Claire's apartment.

97
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,500
出事了
Something's up.

98
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:53,900
麻烦
Excuse me.

99
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,000
借过
Excuse me.

100
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:16,700
- Finch - Reese先生
- Finch. - Mr. Reese.

101
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,300
你说过那机器能给我们号码和时间
You said the machine would give us the number and time.

102
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:22,800
它没有
It didn't.

103
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:20,700
我们知道些什么?
So what do we got?

104
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,500
受害者叫Claire Ryan
Victim's name is Claire Ryan.

105
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:25,000
某方面的教授 独居
Some kind of professor. Lived alone.

106
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:31,900
看起来她遭到殴打
Looks like she was beaten up.

107
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,400
一枪射中头部 近距离
One shot to the head, close range.

108
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,400
她似乎手头宽裕
Looks like she came into some money.

109
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,800
蓝光播放器 全新的 鞋子
BluRay player, new tablet, shoes.

110
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:46,200
昂贵的鞋...周仰杰 莫罗・伯拉尼克
Expensive shoes- Jimmy Choo, Manolo Blahnik.

111
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,800
都是今天早晨买的
All bought this morning.

112
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:53,000
我们还知道什么有关受害者的? 我问了你一个问题 Fusco
What else do we know about our vic? I asked you a question, Fusco.

113
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,500
什么? 什么问题?
What? What's that?

114
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,000
我在Claire这完事了 Finch
I'm done at Claire's, Finch.

115
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,500
我需要你回到街上
I need you out on the street.

116
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:02,000
你要帮我注意剩下的三个
You got to help me get eyes on the remaining three.

117
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,500
我留在这更有用 试图找出他们之间的联系
I'm more useful here, trying to find connections between them.

118
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:06,400
如果他们都死了找出来也没有用
No point in that if they're all dead.

119
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:09,200
跟踪别人是你的专业领域
Tracking people down is your area of expertise.

120
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:13,200
我没法跟踪三个 也不想再失去任何人
I can't track three people down, and I don't want to lose anyone else.

121
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,500
我这里需要你
I need you out here.

122
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:17,700
我马上来
I'm on my way.

123
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:18,900
我盯Wendy
I'll take Wendy.

124
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,800
让Fusco找Paula
Put Fusco on Paula.

125
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:24,100
- 你能跟踪Matt么? - 可以
Can you track Matt? I can track Matt.

126
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,200
马上去
On my way.

127
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,300
你到底在这里干什么?
What the hell are you doing here?

128
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,900
你没有杀了她是么?
You didn't kill her, did you?

129
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:35,000
Lionel 我们一起经历这么多
Lionel, after all we've been through.

130
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,200
没错
Exactly.

131
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,700
你为什么不和Carter一起工作?
Why aren't you working with Carter?

132
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:40,100
她要做文书工作直到我们的杀人犯落网
She's on desk duty till our homicide gets cleaned up.

133
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:43,600
某个不知名的枪手 让她的整个世界充满了悲痛
Some unknown gunman caused her a world of grief.

134
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,600
你不会碰巧知道这些吧?
You wouldn't happen to know anything about that, would you?

135
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,700
不 找到这个叫Paula的女孩
No. Find this girl Paula.

136
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:50,300
地址在背面
Address is on the back.

137
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:52,400
时刻注意她
Keep your eyes on her.

138
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:55,700
Paula Vasquez? 为什么?
Paula Vasquez? Why?

139
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,400
不想让她像楼上的那位女士一样结局
Don't want her ending up like the lady upstairs.

140
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,600
你觉得她也会?
You think she might?

141
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:03,800
我知道她不会 因为你会挡住子弹
I know she won't, because you'll throw yourself in front of the bullet.

142
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,500
真风趣
Funny guy.

143
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,800
我本应该调查的凶杀案呢?
What about the homicide I'm supposed to be investigating?

144
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:10,500
Paula可能和你的凶杀案有联系
Paula could be connected to your homicide.

145
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:11,800
看住她
Stay on her.

146
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:26,300
- 谁动了我的桌子? - Carter 进来
Who messed with my desk? Carter. In here.

147
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:36,000
你对你那特种部队的家伙还了解些什么?
What else have you got on your special forces guy?

148
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:39,400
我了解的一切都在他看的文档里了
Everything I got is in the file he's reading.

149
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,500
无论他是谁
Whoever he is.

150
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,900
你已经追了这家伙几个月了
You've been after this guy for months.

151
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,600
你连个描述都没有?
You don't even have a description?

152
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,900
他很高 穿着一套西装
He- He's tall. He wears a suit.

153
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:48,000
有时候骑摩托车 就这样
Sometimes rides a motorcycle. That's it.

154
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,400
这很严重 Carter
This is serious, Carter.

155
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:52,700
你让他逃掉了 他变成了整个部门的问题了
You letting him run, you've made him a problem for the whole department.

156
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:54,600
我没有让他逃掉
I did not let him run.

157
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,700
我一直在努力抓那混蛋
I've been trying to catch the son of a bitch.

158
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,500
他枪击了你的秘密线人?
Did he shoot your CI?

159
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,500
我知道他是谁之前不会回答这个
I'm not answering that until I know who he is.

160
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:05,100
回答问题不然就把警徽交出来
Answer the question or turn in your badge.

161
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,900
是的 是他
Yes, it was him.

162
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:18,000
这就行了嘛 探员
That will be all, Detective.

163
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:21,900
Finch 我在Wendy的发廊
Finch, I'm at Wendy's salon.

164
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,100
看起来很正常
Seems fine.

165
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,200
等一下
Hang on a sec.

166
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,600
请签名
Signature, please.

167
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:47,400
谢谢
Thank you.

168
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,400
麻烦让一下
Excuse me.

169
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,700
有什么能为您服务的?
Can I help you?

170
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:57,200
我...要预约
I... Need to make an appointment.

171
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,400
洗和剪?
Wash and cut?

172
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,600
来点更潮流的?
Something a little more modern?

173
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:01,800
造型?
Bit of styling?

174
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:07,200
这个灰色是天生的还是染的?
<i>Is this, uh, gray, au naturel or au bouteille?</i>

175
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:11,600
- 是... - 不论怎样都很性感
It's, uh- Sexy either way.

176
