00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,400
我只是想预约
I just need an appointment.

181
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,200
对不起
I'm sorry,

182
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:29,100
但我不能让你就这样回到街上
but I'm not letting you back out on the street looking like this.

183
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,000
该死!
Damn it!

184
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:27,600
Reese先生 我正在跟踪Matt Duggan
Mr. Reese, I'm tracking our friend Matt Duggan.

185
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:30,600
他似乎正在经历早期中年危机
Looks like he's having an early midlife crisis.

186
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:34,400
他刚刚辞掉工作现在在买摩托车
He just quit his job and now he's shopping for motorcycles.

187
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:35,800
等一下
Hold on.

188
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:40,000
我波士顿的阿姨死了 留给我很大一笔零花钱
My aunt in Boston died, left me a nice chunk of change.

189
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:43,200
觉得该奖励自己一个梦想
Thought I'd treat myself to a dream.

190
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,100
不会太久的 亲爱的
Won't be a minute, hon.

191
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:48,700
没错 他给自己买了辆新的杜卡迪
Yep, he's buying himself a new Ducati.

192
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,300
现金付款
Paying cash.

193
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:53,200
被害的Claire也有大笔花销
Murdered woman Claire was spending big too.

194
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,200
看看周围  Finch
Look around, Finch.

195
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,100
有人在监视你的人么?
Is anyone watching your guy?

196
00:12:57,500 --> 00:13:00,300
我对这个不太在行
I'm not exactly good at this.

197
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:13,200
没有 我没看到
No, no one I can see.

198
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,800
仔细观察
Well, keep your eyes open.

199
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,400
回头给我电话
Call me back.

200
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,300
Lionel?
Lionel?

201
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,700
是我 那个叫Paula的女孩? 我跟丢她了
Yeah, that Paula girl? I lost her.

202
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,000
她把我甩掉了
She gave me the slip.

203
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,700
干得好 探员
Well, good work, Detective.

204
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:28,000
对不起 好么?
I'm sorry, okay?

205
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:31,700
还有一件事 我觉得她买了枪支
Look, another thing. I think she bought a firearm.

206
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:34,700
你跟丢了她 她还带着武器?
You lost her and she weaponed up?

207
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,200
你最好还是做你的...
You better stick to your...

208
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,300
日常工作去吧
Day job.

209
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,200
抱歉
Excuse me.

210
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,200
- 我在等Wendy - 对不起
- I'm waiting for Wendy. - I'm sorry.

211
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,300
她有急事走了
She had an emergency, had to rush off.

212
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:47,200
我有空 现在就能帮你
I'm free. I can fit you in now.

213
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,200
不 不用了 谢谢
No, that's okay. Thank you.

214
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,800
Finch 成果如何?
Hi, um, Finch, what do got?

215
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,800
我们的人正从陈列室里出来
Our man is coming out of the showroom.

216
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,200
留下他的订单 交付定金
Placed his order and left a deposit.

217
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,900
很好 跟着他
Okay, stay on him.

218
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,700
两个女孩都逃掉了
Both girls just gave us the slip.

219
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:02,800
等一下 有人留下了童车
Hold on. Someone left a stroller.

220
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:06,500
- 你在说什么? - 车旁有个婴儿车 我不知道妈妈在...
- What are you talking about? - There's a baby stroller near the car. I don't know where the mom-

221
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:09,100
哦 她在
Oh, there she is.

222
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,700
天哪 是炸弹!
Oh, my God, it's a bomb!

223
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,900
趴下 趴到地上 Finch
Get down. Get down on the ground, Finch.

224
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:16,000
我要去警告他!
I have to warn him!

225
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:23,000
Finch 你还好么?
Finch, are you okay?

226
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:25,100
Harold!
Harold!

227
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,500
我看见了 我看到车祸了
I saw it. I saw the crash.

228
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,000
天啊 他死了
Oh, my God. He's dead.

229
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,800
那是什么?
What's that stuff?

230
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,300
我猜是可卡因
Uh, I think it's cocaine.

231
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:10,500
我该更快注意到的
I should have seen it quicker.

232
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,200
什么样的妈妈会把童车留下呢?
I mean, what kind of a mother leaves a stroller?

233
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:16,200
她还戴着墨镜和围巾 明显是为了挡住脸
And she was wearing sunglasses and a scarf, obviously to hide her face.

234
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,100
- Finch - 要是我能警告他 他或许还能活着
- Finch. - If I could have warned him, - he might still be here. - Finch.

235
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:20,400
Finch 你没法救他
You couldn't have saved him.

236
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,000
放手吧
You have to let it go.

237
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:25,300
我们得专注于那些还活着的人
We have to concentrate on the ones still alive.

238
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:26,900
- Wendy和Paula - 对
- Wendy and Paula. - Yes.

239
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:29,000
我一直在找联系 什么都没有找到
I've looked for connections, found none.

240
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,300
没有共同的就业史
No shared employment history.

241
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,700
没有社交网络
No social networking.

242
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:33,900
Paula的在线痕迹微乎其微
Paula's online footprint is miniscule,

243
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:37,200
所以她要不就是个偏执狂 要不就是喜欢潜水
so she's either the paranoid sort or she likes to fly beneath the radar-

244
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,400
这两种我都能处得来
Both of which I can relate to.

245
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:40,600
- 但我... - Finch 联系
- But I- - Finch, connections.

246
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:43,400
对 抱歉
Right, I'm sorry.

247
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,800
智能手机不断寻找wifi信号
Smartphones are constantly searching for wi-fi signals.

248
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:49,100
它们会记录最近的一百多个wifi热点
And they keep the last hundred or so wi-fi hot spots in their memory.

249
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:51,400
我正在从Matt Wendy 和Claire的手机里提取
I've extracted that from Matt, Wendy,

250
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:55,300
用它来测算过去24小时里他们去了哪里
and Claire's phones, and I'm using it to plot where our friends went in the last 24 hours

251
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:58,900
来看他们是否有交集
to see if they- To see if they intersect.

252
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:03,700
罗斯福车道 晚上11:57
Roosevelt Drive... 11:57 PM.

253
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:06,700
他们在同一个地点待了4分钟
They were all in the same place for four minutes.

254
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:07,800
为什么?
Why?

255
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:12,000
根据交通部的网站 有一场一人死亡的交通意外
According to the d.O.T. Website, there was a traffic accident with a fatality.

256
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:14,200
死者姓名隐藏
Name of the deceased withheld.

257
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:16,400
这就是我们的联系
That's our connection.

258
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:20,300
其中的三个人 但没有偏执狂Paula
For three of them, but not paranoid Paula.

259
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:23,800
我们没有她的手机 所以我们不知道她那晚在哪里
We don't have her phone, so we don't know where she was that night.

260
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,400
Fusco说她买了一把枪 她可能是杀手
Fusco said she bought a gun. She could be our killer.

261
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,500
接下来你要去找Wendy
Then you need to get to Wendy.

262
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:31,600
我试过了 她的公寓是空的 而且已经丢弃了自己的手机
I have tried, but her apartment's empty, and she's abandoned her cell phone.

263
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:35,700
我能找到的唯一亲属 是Wendy住在Putnam县的妈妈Susan 
Only relative I could find- Wendy's mom Susan, lives in Putnam County.

264
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,800
- 你在干吗 Carter? - 我无聊了
- What are you doing, Carter? - I got bored.

265
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:50,000
觉得我能在你的案子上帮点忙
Thought I'd lend you a hand with your case.

266
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:54,300
我把你的受害者Claire Ryan的指纹 在指纹自动识别系统里检查了
I ran your murder victim Claire Ryan's fingerprints through AFIS.

267
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:57,000
他们显示两晚前的那场车祸
They showed up at this car crash two nights ago.

268
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,100
Claire的指纹在那辆车上
Claire's prints were on the car.

269
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:01,300
还有这个人 Matt Duggan
And this guy- Matt Duggan.

270
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:05,000
CSU认为他们是目击者 在试图帮助车里这个人
CSU thinks they were witnesses trying to help this guy in the car,

271
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,200
但他死于冲击
but he was killed on impact.

272
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,000
我一定遗漏了什么 这对我们的案子有什么帮助?
I must have missed something. How does this help our case?

273
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:11,200
Claire死了 还有Matt
Well, Claire's dead, and so is Matt.

274
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,400
昨天丧生于汽车爆炸
Killed in a car explosion yesterday.

275
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,400
这可能是巧合
Which could be a coincidence,

276
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:19,500
除了Matt刚刚为自己买了 一台全新的杜卡迪 现金支付
except Matt had just bought himself a brand-new Ducati, paying cash.

277
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:20,900
Claire也购物了
Claire had been shopping too.

278
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:25,800
所以他们都在车祸现场 都有了钱 都死了
So they're both at the crash, they both get money, they both get dead.

279
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,000
钱一定是车里的
Money must have come from inside the car.

280
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:31,300
- 谁开的车? - 根据CSU报告 是Hallen众议员的儿子 Jamie
Who was driving it? According to CSU, Congressman Hallen's son, Jamie.

281
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,100
Hallen众议员的儿子被杀了?
A congressman's son gets killed?

282
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:33,900
这种事怎么会被掩盖呢?
How does that get hushed up?

283
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:37,200
这位Hallen众议员是华尔街银行调查委员会的
Well, the congressman's on the committee investigating Wall Street banks.

284
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,900
他还是警察工会的朋友
And he's a friend of the police unions.

285
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:40,400
我猜这能得到一些善意
I guess that buys some goodwill.

286
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,800
这是意外么?
Was it an accident?

287
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,400
CSU认为Jamie超速而且吸食了可卡因
CSU thinks Jamie was speeding and on coke.

288
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:51,200
在车里唯一找到的是Jamie运作的 海地孤儿慈善基金会的小册子
The only thing that was found in the car was a brochure for a haitian orphans charity Jamie ran.

289
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:55,900
我要去下市局 查下犯罪监控中心的摄像头拍到了什么
I should go down to 1PP, check out what the cameras at the real time crime center saw.

290
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:59,300
我觉得你该留在办公桌前 就像队长要求的那样
I think you should stay at your desk like the captain told you to.

291
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,800
Lionel 真荣幸
Lionel, what a pleasure.

292
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:19,000
我们的受害者Claire Ryan 和两晚前死于车祸的
Our murder victim Claire Ryan- She connects to Congressman Hallen's son, Jamie.

293
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,000
Hallen众议员的儿子Jamie有联系
Died two nights ago in a car crash.

294
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,400
也许你想要把这个 给你戴眼镜的小朋友
Maybe you want to give this to your little friend with the glasses.

295
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,400
我在这 Fusco探员
I'm here, Detective Fusco.

296
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:27,800
没错 你也好
Yeah, right. Hi to you too.

297
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:31,900
我要说的是Jamie Hallen的车上有两组指纹
Like I was about to say, there were two sets of prints on Jamie Hallen's car.

298
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:33,900
Claire的和Matt Duggan的
Claire's and a Matt Duggan's.

299
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:36,800
- 他被杀害了... - 在昨天的爆炸里
- He got killed- - In an explosion yesterday.

300
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,100
Jamie Hallen在罗斯福车道上出了车祸?
Jamie Hallen crashed on Roosevelt Drive?

301
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:40,200
我以为这本该被掩盖掉的
Thought that was supposed to be hushed.

302
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,600
他们一定是从车祸现场拿到钱的 Finch
Car crash must be where they got the money, Finch.

303
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,200
天哪 有什么是你不知道的么?
Jeez, anything you don't know?

304
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:47,100
有 Carter怎么样了?
Yeah. How's Carter doing?

305
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,100
她还在坚持 你知道么?
She's hanging in there, you know?

306
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,600
但当你被困在办公桌边的时候 是很难完成工作的
But it's hard to do the job when you're stuck on your desk.

307
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:54,300
我们会注意她 确保她没事的
We'll keep an eye on her, make sure she's okay.

308
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:58,200
还有探员 你和Hallen议员 谈的时候把手机开着
And Detective, leave your phone on when you talk to Congressman Hallen.

309
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,100
你一直能听到我说话?
You can hear me all the time?

310
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:03,400
是 但我听到更多的是你的肠道
Yes, and I'm hearing rather too much of your lower intestine.

311
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,300
你能把手机从腰带移到上衣口袋么?
Could you possibly move your phone from your belt to your jacket pocket?

312
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,700
嘿 Fusco 你死在那了?
Hey, Fusco, you die in there?

313
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,200
准备好 我来了
Keep your panties on, I'm coming.

314
00:19:14,100 --> 00:19:16,300
如果有我能帮上忙的 请打电话给我
If there's anything I can do, please call me.

315
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:17,200
谢谢你 Davis
Thank you, Davis.

316
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,400
非常感谢
Thank you very much.

317
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:21,800
再次对您的悲痛表示深切的同情 议员
And again, deepest sympathies for your loss, Congressman.

318
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:22,600
谢谢
Appreciate it. Thank you.

319
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:23,800
警察 先生
The police, sir.

320
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,000
探员Olson和Fiasco
Detectives Olson and Fiasco.

321
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:28,700
Fusco
Fusco.

322
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,500
