I didn't like it either, but I couldn't control my son's social life.

331
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:56,300
令郎当天晚上随身带着很多钱?
You son have a lot of money on him that night?

332
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:57,900
我不清楚
I have no idea.

333
00:19:58,300 --> 00:19:59,700
这有什么关系?
Why would that be pertinent?

334
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:00,800
有两个人被杀了
Two people were murdered.

335
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,200
我们认为他们都在事故现场
We think they were both at the crash site.

336
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,100
我们还认为他们在车里找到了钱
We also think they found money in the car.

337
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,900
对不起 我没什么可说的
I'm sorry. I don't know what to say.

338
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:10,100
他在贩毒么?
Was he dealing drugs?

339
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,000
你瞧 他已经死了
Look, he's dead.

340
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,400
我们不能在这件事上就算了么?
Can't we just let it go at that?

341
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,700
还有另外两个人也死了 所以 不行
Two other people are dead too. So, no.

342
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,600
他有贩毒么?
Was he dealing?

343
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,600
我很担心他...
I worried that he- he-

344
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:29,000
他在做些不该做的事情
He was doing something he shouldn't be doing.

345
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,100
他在和一些
He was dealing with people

346
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:33,200
不该打交道的人来往
he shouldn't have been dealing with.

347
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,200
我能说的就这些了
That's all I can say about it.

348
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,900
我们得和Bannerman谈谈了
Well, we'll have to talk to Bannerman.

349
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:40,700
鉴于你对他所说的不能全信
As long as you take what he says to you with a grain of salt.

350
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:42,100
我们不是朋友
We're not friends.

351
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:46,400
我们在令郎的车里发现了一张这个
One of these were found in your son's car.

352
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,400
他建立的这个基金会么?
Did he set up this charity?

353
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,300
是的
Yes, he did.

354
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:51,900
我乐于这样想他
That's how I like to think of him.

355
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,300
他的善行
His good deeds.

356
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:58,200
离开Bannerman家后 你没有回家
You left Bannerman's house, but you weren't going home,

357
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,400
是吧 Jamie?
were you, Jamie?

358
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:54,100
这台新手机 你拿着用
Here is your new phone, okay?

359
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:57,500
- 谢了 你告诉妈妈了吗? - 等我们脱险后再说吧
Thanks. Did you say anything to mom? Not till I know that we're safe.

360
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:59,400
Matt出事了 知道吗?
Did you hear about that guy Matt?

361
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:01,500
我们被人盯上了
There's people looking for us.

362
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:03,400
知道不?
Okay?

363
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:08,000
别过来 小心挨枪子
You get back, or I will shoot you.

364
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,700
买枪前...
If you're going to buy a gun...

365
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,500
先得学会使枪
Make sure you know how to use it.

366
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:19,000
你来过发廊
You came to the salon.

367
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:20,800
你想怎样?
What do you want?

368
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,400
除理发以外吗?
You mean apart from a haircut?

369
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,700
你们俩怎么认识对方的?
How do you two know each other?

370
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:26,600
我们俩认识好些年了
We've known each other for years.

371
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,200
我们是一对被收养的姐妹
We're foster sisters.

372
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:30,700
这与你无关
Not that that's any of your business.

373
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:33,700
你们从撞毁轿车上
Guess the, uh, money you took from the crashed car

374
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:35,500
找到的那笔钱 也与我无关咯?
is none of my business either?

375
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:41,700
我们得先弄清你的来历 否则无可奉告
We're not telling you anything, till we know who you are and why you're following us.

376
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:49,100
- 有人在吗? - 问问他来路
Hello! Anyone at home? Find out what he wants.

377
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:50,600
别靠近大门
And stand away from the door.

378
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:56,600
你是谁?
Who is it?

379
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,900
我叫Dayne
Uh, my name is Dayne.

380
00:22:57,900 --> 00:23:00,800
很抱歉打扰了 我小车抛锚了
I'm sorry to trouble you, but my car has just broken down.

381
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:04,300
抱歉 这不是修车店
I'm sorry, but this isn't a garage.

382
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:07,900
我知道 可我手机没电了
I know, I know, but the thing is- is my phone just died

383
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:12,200
孩子们吓坏了 电话能借我用用吗?
and the kids are getting kind of scared, so if I could just use your phone?

384
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:14,100
我会付你话费的
I- I'll pay for the call.

385
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:15,800
让他进来
Let him in.

386
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:17,300
好吧
Okay.

387
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:01,400
这是Jamie Hallen遇害的录像 
Here's how Jamie Hallen died.

388
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:07,600
从犯罪监控中心的技术人员那弄来的
I persuaded a tech at the real time crime center to copy this for me.

389
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,700
两辆轿车停在了事故现场
Two cars stopped after the crash.

390
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,400
中心工作人员可以识别车牌号
Crime center guys were able to read the plates.

391
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:17,100
前面那辆车主是Claire Ryan 跟随其后的是Matt Duggan
Prius registered to Claire Ryan, escort to Matt Duggan,

392
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:18,600
两人身份已经确认
so they're confirmed.

393
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:20,700
注意这里
But look at this.

394
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,800
- 两个女人 - 没错
- Two more women. - Mm-hmm.

395
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,100
- 身份确认了吗? - 没有
- Crime center identify them? - Nope.

396
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:27,200
镜头设置为最大视场
Camera's set for maximum field of view.

397
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:30,400
分辨率不足识别面部
Resolution's not enough for facial recognition.

398
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,800
接下来才是关键
This is where it gets interesting.

399
00:24:35,700 --> 00:24:37,700
手提箱 肯定是那笔钱
Suitcase. That has to be the money.

400
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:41,100
必须先杀手一步 找到这两个女人
We got to find these girls before the killers do.

401
00:24:41,700 --> 00:24:45,000
中心的人说 有一名探员也在找她们
Guy at the crime center said there's another detective looking for them.

402
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:47,500
82辖区的Foster探员 
Detective Foster, 82nd precinct.

403
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:49,100
还有别的线索吗?
We got anything else?

404
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:50,800
这个男人
Yeah. This guy.

405
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:54,700
事发约30分钟后 他打了通电话
About 30 minutes after the crash, he makes a phone call.

406
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:57,000
能监听通话内容就好了
Wish we could hear what he was saying.

407
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,500
可惜 这不是国家安全局
Unfortunately, we're not the NSA.

408
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:01,800
这肯定是新车 瞧
Vehicle must be new, 'cause look.

409
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:03,500
还没上牌呢
There are no plates.

410
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:04,700
这么一来就省事了
That's convenient.

411
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,100
想接手这个案子吗 Carter?
Want to get in some more trouble, Carter?

412
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:13,600
找Foster探员谈谈 看他知道什么
Go talk to Detective Foster, and see if he knows anything.

413
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,800
乐意效劳
Be a pleasure.

414
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:33,600
Finch
Finch,

415
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,900
能查查圣乔治医院的病人Susan McNally吗?
can you do a search for Susan McNally at St. George's hospital?

416
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:38,900
在查呢
I'm on it.

417
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:42,400
情况如何?
Everything all right?

418
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:45,100
杀手想干掉Wendy和Paula
Killers just tried to take out Wendy and Paula.

419
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:46,400
但愿没有成功
Please tell me they failed.

420
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,300
她们暂时逃过一劫
For now. Girls took off.

421
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:51,700
她们是一对被收养的姐妹
They're sisters, Finch. Foster sisters.

422
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:55,600
如果她们的养母还在圣乔治医院 我想她们会去那的
If their mom's still at St. George's, that's where I think they'll go.

423
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:59,900
- 养母还在那 - 她生病了吗? 所以需要那笔钱?
- Mom is still there. - So she's sick? That why the girls took the money?

424
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:01,500
摔了一跤 伤了屁股
Had a fall, broke her hip.

425
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:03,500
倒也不是生病
Not sick exactly.

426
00:26:04,300 --> 00:26:06,100
她的房子才是关键
Her home is the problem.

427
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:08,500
按揭超出了房产价值
Mortgage is worth more than the house.

428
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,900
银行要收了这房子
Bank's foreclosing on her.

429
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:11,700
至少她们拿钱是有因的
At least they took the money for a reason.

430
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,400
- 查到那笔钱的主人是谁了吗? - 还在查呢
- You know whose it is yet? - I'm digging.

431
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:16,400
保证她们的安全
Keep those girls safe.

432
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:21,800
Fusco 是我Carter 刚去了82辖区
Fusco, Carter. Just left the 82nd.

433
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,900
压根没有什么Foster探员
There is no Detective Foster.

434
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:29,000
这是障眼法 误导我们以录像作线索
Somebody used a fake detective shield to get eyes on the crash footage.

435
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:33,800
记得Claire的案子吗 ?
Remember how Claire was beaten up?

436
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:38,700
杀手通过车牌号找到了她 折磨她 让她招供同伙
I think the killer tracked her through her license plates, then tortured her to get the other names.

437
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:39,800
再聊
Call me.

438
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:43,100
有毛病啊 跟踪警察?
What's wrong with you, following a cop?

439
00:26:43,100 --> 00:26:45,900
- 想挨枪子? - 只想确保你安全罢了 警探
Trying to get yourself shot? I'm just worried about you, Detective.

440
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:48,600
少来这套 赶紧闪人吧
Don't. Just back off, okay?

441
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:51,400
带上你那衣冠楚楚的朋友
You and your preppy friend over there.

442
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:54,600
找个安静的地方说两句?
Why don't we go somewhere quiet where we can talk?

443
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:58,900
你是中情局的人
You're CIA.

444
00:26:58,900 --> 00:27:01,000
我在伊拉克绿区那会儿接触过不少像你这样的
I met plenty like you in the green zone.

445
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:04,400
你为什么会担心我的安全?
So why are you worried about me?

446
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:06,100
因为你在找那个人
Because of the man you're chasing.

447
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:08,000
他是个危险人物
He's dangerous.

448
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:09,800
他救过我一命
He saved my life.

449
00:27:09,800 --> 00:27:11,800
这你怎么解释 纯属意外?
What was that, an accident?

450
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:14,400
只能说明他良心未泯
No. Just proves he still has good instincts.

451
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:16,800
- 你到底认不认识他?  - 认识
- Do you even know him? - Yeah.

452
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,500
我曾是他最好的朋友
I was his best friend.

453
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:21,500
那为什么还要拿下他?
Then why do you want him so bad?

454
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:23,500
因为他曾为国家卖命
Because he used to kill people for his country.

455
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:25,000
现在却成了杀人狂
Now he just kills them.

456
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:28,600
据我们所知 他干掉许多人
His victims... The ones that we know of.

457
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,400
有时可说是为民除害
For some he deserves a medal.

458
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,700
有时却是滥杀无辜
For some, the chair.

459
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,800
为什么告诉我这些?
Why are you telling me this?

460
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:35,600
我们要你认清他的真面目
'Cause we want you to know who he is.

461
00:27:36,100 --> 00:27:38,700
他是个天生的杀手 头号危险人物
He's an incredibly dangerous, incredibly gifted man

462
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:41,300
他的职业让他痛不欲生
who's been almost destroyed by the things he was made to do.

463
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,400
他总想相信别人
He's always looking for someone to trust,

464
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:47,400
但他生性多疑 不可能信任他人
but his paranoia makes trust impossible.

465
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:50,100
我没听懂你的意思
I don't understand.

466
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:54,600
Kara Stanton是他在中情局的搭档
Kara Stanton- His CIA handler.

467
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:55,800
他们曾是一对默契搭档
They were a team.

468
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,500
合作无间 一起经历过
Inseparable, saved each other's lives

469
00:27:57,500 --> 00:27:59,600
- 无数次出生入死 然而... - 他杀了她
- a dozen times, and then- - He killed her.

470
00:27:59,900 --> 00:28:01,200
而后销声匿迹
Then disappeared.

471
00:28:01,300 --> 00:28:02,600
我们以为他牺牲了
We thought he was dead.

472
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:04,400
为他刻上了烈士之星
Gave him his star on the wall at Langley.

473
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:08,100
3个月前 因为你 他死而复生
Then three months ago, you ran his prints- Brought him back from the dead.

474
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:11,000
我们要逮到他 以免再有杀戮
We want to bring him back in before he kills anyone else.

475
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:13,000
这么做也是为了保护他
Before he kills himself.

476
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:14,800
我们是在帮他
We want to help him.

477
00:28:17,300 --> 00:28:19,300
这与我何干?
So where do I come in to all of this?

478
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:22,300
他信任你
We think he trusts you.

479
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:25,100
就像信任他昔日的同伴一样
Like he trusted her.

480
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:30,000
你要让你俩都活着
We want you to keep yourself, and him, alive.

481
00:28:39,100 --> 00:28:41,100
谢谢合作 Bannerman先生
Thanks for coming in, Mr. Bannerman.

482
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:44,100
纽约警署有何新进展?
Anything for the NYPD.

483
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:48,300
Jamie Hallen前晚参加了你家的派对
Jamie Hallen- He was at a party at your house, two nights ago.

484
00:28:48,300 --> 00:28:49,200
简而言之
Briefly.

485
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,200
他喝醉了
He was stoned.

486
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,400
我把他请出了家门
I asked him to leave.

487
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,900
还替他叫了辆车
Even ordered a cab for him.

488
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:57,300
很遗憾 车还没到他就离开了
He left before it arrived... Sadly.

489
00:28:57,300 --> 00:28:58,600
他在贩毒吗?
Was he dealing drugs?

490
00:28:59,700 --> 00:29:01,500
我喜欢这孩子
Look, I liked the kid.

491
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:04,000
- 但我不想... - 他在贩毒吗?
But I don't want to- Was he dealing drugs?

492
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,100
我不清楚
I don't know.

493
00:29:07,700 --> 00:29:09,900
但他突然间有了一大笔钱
But he seemed to have a lot of money suddenly.

494
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:12,900
这么跟你说吧
And, uh, let's put it like this.

495
00:29:14,100 --> 00:29:17,100
听说他勾搭上了不该惹上的人
I heard he was dealing with some people he shouldn't.

496
00:29:20,700 --> 00:29:22,400
我听到了 Fusco探员
I heard, Detective Fusco.

497
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:24,600
Bannerman的供词印证了Hallen议员的说法
Bannerman's story confirmed Congressman Hallen's.

498
00:29:24,600 --> 00:29:25,800
他俩的说法如出一辙
Yeah, he said the same things.

499
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,900
- 这对我们毫无帮助 - 你没听明白我的意思
- So it doesn't help us. - You're not hearing me.

500
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:30,200
他和Hallen的供词一模一样
He said the same thing as Hallen.

501
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:34,000
凭我经验判断 他们是事先串通好的
Look, I interrogate a lot of douches, and I know when they got their lies lined up.

502
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:35,700
他俩事先统一口径?
They coordinated their stories?

503
00:29:35,700 --> 00:29:37,900
他们不应该是死对头吗?
Despite the fact they're supposed to hate each other?

504
00:29:37,900 --> 00:29:40,600
我认为Bannerman和Hallen在做交易
I think Bannerman was working something with Hallen.

505
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:43,800
Jamie是中间人 现在他们想跟他撇清干系
Jamie was a go-between, and now they're tossing him under the bus.

506
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:55,100
Reese先生?
Mr. Reese?

507
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,300
我在医院
I'm at the hospital.

508
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:00,500
Wendy在这
Wendy's here.

509
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:03,200
Paula不见踪影
No sign of Paula.

510
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:05,400
查到什么了吗?
What do you got?

511
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:06,700
快了
Getting close.

512
00:30:06,700 --> 00:30:09,200
已经查出了Jamie当天晚上的行踪 
I know where Jamie was going that night anyway.

513
00:30:09,700 --> 00:30:11,700
他去了Laguardia机场 
Only as far as Laguardia airport.

514
00:30:11,700 --> 00:30:13,500
- 他要离开这? - 没错
- Was he flying somewhere? - Yes.

515
00:30:13,500 --> 00:30:16,400
他打算坐Davis Bannerman的私人飞机
On a jet belonging to Davis Bannerman.

516
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:19,700
跟联邦航空局报备是飞往开曼群岛
Flight plan to the Caymans filed with the FAA.

517
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:23,200
Jamie Hallen是机上唯一的乘客
Jamie Hallen the only passenger on the manifest.

518
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,600
需要帮忙吗?
Excuse me, can I help you?

519
00:30:25,100 --> 00:30:26,400
在找人吗?
Are you looking for someone?

520
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:28,600
已经找到了 谢谢
Just found him. Thanks.

521
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:31,900
